frameDefinitions: An Item is in a state of dryness.
A Container  is in a state of fullness/emptiness with respect to some Contents.
A Useful_location is accessible to some (possibly generic)
The words in this frame refer to what Clothing the Wearer (or a specific Body_part of the Wearer) has on.
An Entity loses moisture with the outcome of being in a dry state.
frameExamples: John carried a bucket <t>full</t> of water.
I left the door to the lobby <t>open</t> for you.
I <t>had</t> <t>on</t> the most ridiculous monkey-suit you could imagine.
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Item</fen> exists in a state of dryness.
<fen>Container</fen> is used for the entity whose fullness is being described.
The <fen>Theme</fen> whose motion is blocked or free.
The place or thing that the <fen>Theme</fen> is headed towards, despite a potential or actual <fen>Barrier</fen>.
An entity that (at least potentially) prevents the <fen>Theme</fen> from getting to the <fen>Useful_location</fen>.
The time when the <fen>Useful_location</fen> is or is not accessible.
The person whose clothing is under discussion.
This role identifies the <fen>Clothing</fen> that the <fen>Wearer</fen> wears.
The body part of the <fen>Wearer</fen> which is covered by the <fen>Clothing</fen>.
The time at or during which the <fen>Wearer</fen> has the <fen>Clothing</fen> on.
The <fen>Entity</fen> is the thing that loses moisture and becomes dry.
The location where the <fen>Entity</fen> becomes dry.
listRoleExamples: She was wearing a glove <fex>on one hand</fex>.
<fex>By five o'clock</fex>, he was wearing the old holey jeans and t-shirt again.
